      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "ae64dc8e3a9ac8d6",
      "text": "__Ceramic__ is a protocol for an interoperable, user-centric web. Ceramic stores verifiable, append-only documents on IPFS and anchors them into any blockchain for consensus. Ceramic documents are a core building block for the permissionless web, as they can be modeled to represent self-sovereign identities, schemas, policies, and much more.\n\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "02aaf3bb5fbe9cf4",
      "text": "Ceramic is ideal for storing information that requires guaranteed trust, cross-platform interoperability, and multi-party consumption.\n"
    },
    {
